---
---

<section class="section border-t border-ink-800/80">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink-800 bg-gradient-to-br from-ink-900 to-ink-950 p-10 text-center md:p-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight2 md:text-3xl">Try it in 60 seconds</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-xl text-sm text-ink-400">
        Public alpha. Apache 2.0. Built for any team with a TypeScript backend that
        wants to expose itself to AI agents the right way.
      </p>
      <div class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-md rounded-lg border border-ink-800 bg-ink-950/80 px-4 py-3 text-left font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-ink-500">$</span> npx @mcify/cli@alpha init my-mcp
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-col items-center gap-3 md:flex-row md:justify-center">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="https://docs.mcify.dev/start/install/">Read the docs</a>
        <a
          class="btn-secondary"
          href="https://github.com/Lelemon-studio/mcify"
          rel="noreferrer noopener"
          target="_blank"
        >
          View on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 border-t border-ink-800 pt-6">
        <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-xs text-ink-500">
          The whole docs site is also available as
          <a class="text-accent hover:underline" href="https://docs.mcify.dev/llms-full.txt">/llms-full.txt</a>
          — paste that URL into Claude or Cursor and the model has every page in context.
          Try the
          <a class="text-accent hover:underline" href="https://docs.mcify.dev/prompts/how-to-use/">copy-paste AI prompts</a>
          for adding tools and wrapping APIs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
